# SPA fallback for Cloudflare Pages. With web.output "single" the app is one
# index.html hydrated client-side; serve it for any path so deep links and
# refreshes on routes like /sign-in resolve instead of 404ing.
#
# Note: the static privacy.html is already served at /privacy by Cloudflare's clean-URL
# canonicalisation, and static assets take precedence over this catch-all, so a crawler hitting
# /privacy gets the real policy. Do NOT add a `/privacy /privacy.html 200` rule, it loops against
# that canonicalisation (/privacy -> /privacy.html -> 308 -> /privacy -> ...).
